Port to Linux 6.18 investigation: dpa_app_wrapper (package/network/ask-dpa-app/files/dpa_app_wrapper)
already supports capturing dpa_app's stdout/stderr to /tmp/dpa_app.log
when ASK_DPA_APP_DEBUG is set, but the kernel only ever launches it via
call_usermodehelper() with a fixed envp[] that doesn't set that variable.
So at real boot, dpa_app's output (including libfmc's own per-scheme PCD
error detail) is silently discarded -- nothing reaches dmesg/logread, and
no /tmp/dpa_app.log is ever created.

Add ASK_DPA_APP_DEBUG=1 to the usermode helper's envp[] so the wrapper's
existing logging path is exercised on every real boot. Diagnostic-only:
does not change any FMan/PCD programming behavior.

--- a/cdx-5.03.1/cdx_main.c
+++ b/cdx-5.03.1/cdx_main.c
@@ -85,6 +85,10 @@
 		"HOME=/",
 		"TERM=linux",
 		"PATH=/sbin:/usr/sbin:/bin:/usr/bin",
+		/* Route dpa_app's real stdout/stderr to /tmp/dpa_app.log via
+		 * dpa_app_wrapper, which is otherwise silently discarded by
+		 * call_usermodehelper. */
+		"ASK_DPA_APP_DEBUG=1",
 		NULL
 	};
 	/*
